description: Competed nationally at the UN Youth Public Speaking Competition. Competed and won the Lions Youth Of the year awards on a state level
Elected as the School Vice Captain for my High School.
Competed nationally for state and national levels for Rotary Youth, and became Young person in STEM of the year
Graduated high school in the top 1%, with a university entrance rank of 97.5.
Started my degree in Computer Science at UNSW. Was 1 of 4 members in Australia to receive the Co-op Scholarship ($21600 p.a.).
Became a software engineering intern at Rntr, a climate tech startup focusing on improving the circular fashion network.
Did a ted talk about the power of smaller decisions in creating our legacy and impact
Interned at Berowra's Federal MP, Julian Lesser's Office focusing on data analytics software to understand telecommunications issues. Ran community events as well.
Became a Technology Advisory Intern for the State Parlimentarian, The Hon. Jacqui Munro advising on AI insights and tools
Started a software Engineering internship at Mutinex (Series A, raised 17.5M)
Was one of 20 global student entrepreneurs selected for the Emerging Giants Summit in Sydney, meeting founders, VCs, and operators in the Sydney Ecosystem.
Selected to join Next Chapter - a private community for the next ambitous young people
Ran an AI Ethics Event and Community platform to elevate the voices of those in development and policy and have an interdisciplinary conversation
